FBIS4-53146 "dreas095_n_94006" FBIS-EAS-94-095 Daily Report 14 May 1994 Vietnam Mobil To Implement Contract Signed with Vietnam Mobil To Implement Contract Signed with Vietnam OW1505105394 Hanoi Voice of Vietnam in Mandarin 0830 GMT 14 May 94 OW1505105394 Hanoi Voice of Vietnam Mandarin BFN [From the "News" program] [Text] After 19 years, the U.S. Mobil Oil Company has returned to Vietnam to make investments and start operation in Vietnam. A responsible person of the company recently said that the company would strive to make preparations to start oil prospecting in waters near Vietnam's Truong Sa [Spratly] Islands as quickly as possible. On 12 May, a U.S. Mobil Oil Company spokesman said the company would continue to implement the contract signed with Vietnam and explore and prospect for oil together with their Vietnamese counterpart in the Thanhlong area within Vietanam's territorial waters, and that the first oil well would be drilled within the next few months. The above statement was made by the U.S. Mobil Oil Company in reply to the latest statement issued by the Chinese side.
